                    "max_tokens": 400,
                    "goals": [
                        "Maintain naval dominance of the English Channel and North Sea (deny German naval expansion).",
                        "Protect home supply centers (LON, EDI, LVP) and secure nearby seas (ENG, NTH, YOR/CLY options).",
                        "Open a quiet, flexible Anglo\u2011French understanding to avoid costly Channel friction and to check German sea power.",
                        "Avoid premature, large continental commitments \u2014 keep options open to pivot to Scandinavia or the Atlantic as the board develops.",
                        "Monitor Russia and Germany for Baltic/North Sea threats; be prepared to adjust fleet posture if KIE or Russian Baltic units move toward the North Sea."
                    ],
                    "relationships": {
                        "TURKEY": "Neutral",
                        "GERMANY": "Unfriendly",
                        "AUSTRIA": "Neutral",
                        "ITALY": "Neutral",
                        "RUSSIA": "Neutral",
                        "FRANCE": "Ally"
                    },
                    "full_private_diary": [
                        "[S1901M] No prior messages or binding agreements. No commitments made. My immediate posture is maritime and cautious: I will seek a quick, quiet understanding with France to keep the English Channel and Western approaches peaceful (offer: I will not contest Brest/Irish Sea if France does not contest the Channel/North Sea). I will signal to Germany that aggressive naval moves from Kiel toward the North Sea/Bight will be met by English fleet concentration; to Russia that Baltic moves which threaten the North Sea will be watched. Key point for future self: there are no promises to other powers yet \u2014 plan to open talks with France first about non\u2011aggression in the Channel and flexible support against any single continental hegemon.\nIntent: Planned orders for S1901M: F LON -> ENG; F EDI -> NTH; A LVP -> YOR. I intend to carry these out. I will communicate these moves as my proposed posture (defensive maritime control) to France and Germany: ask France to avoid a move into the Channel/English fleet areas and ask Germany to avoid naval pressure from KIE into the North Sea. If France behaves aggressively toward my Channel fleet (moves to ENG or supports into ENG), I will reassess and contest Channel approaches.",
                        "[S1901M] S1901M \u2014 Carried out the planned maritime posture: fleets out of London and Edinburgh toward the Channel/North Sea, Liverpool army toward Yorkshire. No messages, no overt French challenge to the Channel and no recorded German naval pressure from Kiel this turn \u2014 no betrayals detected. That quiet is an advantage: my fleets now patrol the approaches and can deter German Bight/North Sea expansion. Main risk remains untested: Germany\u2019s intentions from KIE and any Russian Baltic drift. Lesson: convert this tacit understanding with France into a short, clear non\u2011aggression note for the Channel, and quietly warn Germany that any KIE\u2192NTH/HEL move will see rapid English concentration. Keep continental commitments light; preserve naval flexibility."
                    ],
